    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Right Step by I.O.C.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bertrand Horwitz letter praises International Olympic Committee for banning Afghanistan from Sydney Games because it bans women from sports0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>It is interesting that the International Olympic Committee has banned Afghanistan from participating in the Sydney Games because, among other things, the country bans women from sports (Sports Plus, Aug. 7). I wish the I.O.C. had been equally concerned about fairness and idealism for the Berlin Games 64 years ago when the German government forbade a section of its population from participating.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>It is interesting that the International Olympic Committee has banned Afghanistan from participating in the Sydney Games because, among other things, the country bans women from sports (Sports Plus, Aug. 7). I wish the I.O.C. had been equally concerned about fairness and idealism for the Berlin Games 64 years ago when the German government forbade a section of its population from participating.</p>
        <p>The I.O.C.'s current action is a step toward the ideal that the Olympics represent.</p>
        <p>BERTRAND HORWITZ  Vestal, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
